OL,3,CThe seaside town hit by infected
OL,4,Cdrinking water and misinformation
OL,6,FThere were reports of people falling
OL,7,Fill with mysterious symptoms; members
OL,8,Fof the public were advised to boil
OL,9,Ftheir tap water before drinking it. An
OL,10,Finformation vacuum was flooded with
OL,11,Frumours, speculation and thousands of
OL,12,Fsocial media posts.
OL,14,FDeepening crisis
OL,16,FThe more time went on, the more the
OL,17,Fcrisis deepened. Maps of the region
OL,18,Fwere painstakingly analysed; roads
OL,19,Fwere closed and car parks
OL,20,Frequisitioned; bottled water became a
OL,21,Fprecious commodity.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
