OL,3,CThe seaside town hit by infected
OL,4,Cdrinking water and misinformation
OL,6,FTanya became the unofficial spokesman
OL,7,Ffor her community, painstakingly
OL,8,Feducating herself on the intricate
OL,9,Fdetails of Cryptosporidiosis, poring
OL,10,Fover charts and graphs on the South
OL,11,FWest Water website.
OL,13,FMichaela, too, used her anger and
OL,14,Ffrustration to push for improvements.
OL,15,FBoth women had young families who were
OL,16,Fshowing symptoms of the illness, and
OL,17,Fthey told me they would not rest until
OL,18,Fthe company had issued a proper
OL,19,Fapology and full compensation.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/13
