OL,3,CThe seaside town hit by infected
OL,4,Cdrinking water and misinformation
OL,6,FMaureen Blake told us: "I still buy
OL,7,Fbottled water. I just won't take the
OL,8,Frisk."
OL,10,FDiane Plowman said: "I don't trust the
OL,11,Ftap water at all, I will never use it.
OL,12,FI use it in the kettle, to boil, but I
OL,13,Fwill never drink it."
OL,15,FBut Sue Swanston said: "I find it
OL,16,Ffine. My husband and I both drink tap
OL,17,Fwater, we haven't got any worries
OL,18,Fabout it. We've got faith in what
OL,19,Fthey've done and what they've put in
OL,20,Fplace."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/13
